latestIgtvVideos.title: Pregnancy Reveal: Part 2
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Here comes the second reveal that we wanted to do for our friends. We wanted to break the news to them personally & I am quite proud of us that we could keep this secret. We actually kind of cut down our video calls with friends cos our party pooper Avi was around. He knew this is not to be told to anyone & he would just do the opposite 😂

Now we were back in India & we planned to reveal it on my birthday which was the perfect occasion where no one would suspect. 

Now the question was how to do the reveal, we did not have time in hand, I saw the piñata cake on Instagram and thought this could be it, the cake sizes turned out to be quite small (for the birthday) than expected but our only focus was the reveal which was a hit, so no regrets there! Just so bummed that recording the screen doesn’t capture audio, nevertheless, I have a good bank of memories 💗

If only I could turn back time & change things so that my dad could know about this, about Ava & play with them. But life is not perfect & hunky dory like you would think. There always is a feeling of incompleteness & void but I believe he is watching over us, our guiding angel 😇

@iamjayshah
.
Heart shaped piñata: Special thanks to @tbakersaffair who delivered this to me in only a couple of hours 😘 💗
.
Chocolate Piñata: @cacaoandmeindia

latestIgtvVideos.title: Pregnancy Reveal: Part 1
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Firstly, I am so glad & so grateful that I was with my family when we got to know that we are pregnant & I could make them a part
of this especially my mom ❤️ . I wanted to keep it a surprise for Jay (which was such a bummer) because we had had false alarms a couple of times. I am sure if you are planning for a baby you know what I am saying!

So I checked on the strip and saw a double line, I thought it was false since the strips were expired & I felt this was impossible because truth be, we were actually on a break from the whole planning jing-bang & I was here to help around with my sister’s pregnancy & her baby. So I kind of kept this sealed with me for an entire day & checked on several expired strips throughout the day. Hahah! 

Finally when all the strips tested positive, I broke the news to my mom & my sister. My mom rushed to the pharmacy to get a valid pregnancy testing kit. She reached the store & realised that she had forgotten her wallet + cards at home. Now she drove all the way back & forth to get this done. Finally, I did a quick check on it & THERE IT WAS!! DOUBLE LINE!

Next was, how do I break the news to Jay? Who was the most excited about getting a ‘baby on board’. I was absolutely cluless & particularly on that day Jay was in such an irritated mood which he rarely or may be never is. I was actually planning to skip on telling him that day which was absolutely absurd. But then came in action my sister & her ideas💡. She put my strip in a branded alcohol pouch, the pouch went into an Amazon box which wasn’t even taped. LOL. Thats called being impulsive! My mom invited my brother & brother-in-law to the living area without any rhyme or reason, they were all confused. 

My confused, inquisitive brother-in-law comes up to Jay & asks him - “Why did they call us up here?” & enters my sister with the untaped Amazon box placing it right in Jay’s hands. Jay, he instantly caught that something is fishy & the rest is all captured for you to see. 

For my brother's reaction who is so fed up of kids, now time for the third one Mamu!

PS: Jay did have an idea - he never pays attention to trash but this time he spotted my discarded strip cover in the bin.

I think the universe has a funny way of rearranging things for you. @aianajsays and I had such a blast on this trip, we ate yummy food, trekked, soaked in nature & just spent time ✨

It never gets easier, does it? 🥹

Mom guilt can really make you question your ability as a mom - whether you’re doing enough or whether you’re doing it right? It’s a constant battle but I’ve realised that we’re all doing our best and it’s completely okay to take a little time out to yourself and reset ✨

To all the new moms out there, what’s your take on this? Let’s chat in the comments and help each other out 💖

Ps: Taking this moment to be super grateful for all the work opportunities and most importantly, for my strong support system at home, my grandparents, in-laws & @iamjayshah 🫶🏻
